  "body": "In [S05](https://design.perl6.org/S05.html#New_metacharacters) the paragraph starts with \r\n\r\n> As with the disjunctions | and ||, conjunctions come in both & and && ...\r\n\r\nRegex conjunctions also show up in some roast tests (https://github.com/perl6/roast/blob/master/S05-capture/caps.t#L66 and https://github.com/perl6/roast/blob/master/S05-mass/rx.t#L801).\r\n\r\nI don't see any mention in user docs yet.\r\n\r\nI don't claim to understand much but my effort at an example might look like:\r\n```Perl6\r\n> perl6 -e 'say so all(\"lost and found\", \"found and lost\") ~~ /.* found .* & .* lost .*/'\r\nTrue\r\n> perl6 -e 'say so all(\"lost and found\", \"found and lost\", \"there already\") ~~ /.* found .* & .* lost .*/'\r\nFalse\r\n```",
